// __________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
//
// autoexec.cfg - a text file containing custom console commands
// and settings that automatically execute when launching Valve games
// such as Team Fortress 2. It ensures personalized settings - such as 
// custom keybinds, crosshairs, mouse sensitivity - are applied immediately,
// providing a consistent experience and preventing settings from resetting. 
//
// It's crucial for maintaining consistent settings when playing on 
// different computers or after updates because it automates setting up 
// custom configurations (e.g. custom keybinds and graphic settings) 
// without manual entry every session.
// 
// This is my autoexec file which includes different sections with a small
// description following each section.
//
// __________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________











